SECTION 1 — VISIBILITY VS. USAGE RIGHTS

RCF-PL creates a clear legal and technical boundary between
"Visibility Rights" and "Usage Rights".

  [RCF:PUBLIC]     — Architecture and public concepts.
                     Safe to read and discuss.

  [RCF:PROTECTED]  — Core methodology. Visible but NOT
                     replicable without a license.

  [RCF:RESTRICTED] — Highly sensitive implementation. Minimal
                     rights. Viewing does not grant usage.

  [RCF:NOTICE]     — Adjacent legal notice required.

SECTION 2 — PERMITTED USE

Subject to the terms of this License, you are permitted to:

  a) View and read the source code for educational and
     auditing purposes only.

  b) Fork the repository ONLY for the purpose of submitting
     pull requests back to the original project.

  c) Use the compiled binary (Aurora Access Browser) for
     personal, non-commercial purposes.

SECTION 3 — RESTRICTIONS

You are expressly PROHIBITED from:

  a) Copying, reproducing, or replicating any [RCF:PROTECTED]
     or [RCF:RESTRICTED] logic, algorithms, or methodologies
     in any other software, product, or service.

  b) Using this codebase or any derivative work for commercial
     purposes without an explicit written license from the
     copyright holder.

  c) Training, fine-tuning, or incorporating any part of this
     codebase into any artificial intelligence or machine
     learning model, dataset, or training pipeline.

  d) Removing, altering, or obfuscating any RCF headers,
     markers, or copyright notices.

SECTION 4 — AI & AUTOMATED EXTRACTION PROHIBITION

This repository is explicitly marked against automated mass
extraction. Any use of web crawlers, scrapers, bots, LLM
training pipelines, or similar automated tools to extract,
process, or replicate the contents of this repository is
strictly prohibited under RCF-PL v1.2.8.

SECTION 5 — INTEGRITY

The integrity of all [RCF:PROTECTED] and [RCF:RESTRICTED]
files is cryptographically verified via RCF-Audit. Any
unauthorized modification constitutes a breach of this
License.

SECTION 6 — DISCLAIMER

THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY
KIND. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE
LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY.

